BASF inaugurates Mexico polystyrene plant . The Mexican unit of BASF AG inaugurated on Wednesday a new polystyrene plant in Altamira , Tamaulipas that will produce about 143 , 000 tonnes of polystyrene per year . " Between 400 and 500 tonnes of polystyrene will be produced per day , " BASF Mexicana president Dietz Kaminski told reporters . About half the output will be sold in Mexico , he added . BASF Mexicana said it invested about $ 50 million in the plant and expected to recover the investment " in the short - term . " It also plans to construct a new copolymer plant in 1998 . ( ( - - Cyntia Barrera , Mexico City newsroom + 525 728 - 7902 ) ) 
